headline: 2 Reasons to Like BR and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Broadridge has had an impressive run over the past six months. While the S&P 500 has been flat, the stock has returned 11.9% and now trades at $236.94. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
